  "bib_entries": {
    "9434002": {
      "title": "Iteration of maps by an automaton",
      "abstract": "Abstract Let x =( x 1 , x 2 ,\u2026) with the x i elements of afinite set A be an automatic sequence, i.e., x is generated by a tag machine with deletion number one. Let F be a finite set and suppose maps \u03d5 a : F \u2192 F are given for all a\u03f5A . It is shown constructively that the sequence of iterates (\u03d5 x1 , \u03d5 x2 o \u03d5 x1 , \u03d5 x3 o \u03d5 x2 o \u03d5 x1 ,\u2026) is again an automatic sequence."
    }
  }
}